{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":760,"text":"\"Robam kbach boran,\""},{"time":2560,"text":"or the art of Khmer classical dance,"},{"time":4360,"text":"is more than 1,000 years old."},{"time":7000,"text":"It was developed as a prayer in movement"},{"time":9600,"text":"for rain and fertility,"},{"time":11800,"text":"and a prosperity that this meant\nfor an agricultural society."},{"time":17000,"text":"Dancers who were both men and women"},{"time":19760,"text":"were offered to temples"},{"time":21040,"text":"where they served as living bridges\nbetween heaven and earth."},{"time":24800,"text":"Their dancing bodies carried the prayers\nof the people up to the gods,"},{"time":29760,"text":"and the will of the deities\nwas delivered back through them"},{"time":33160,"text":"to the people and the land."}]},{"cues":[{"time":37720,"text":"There are a lot of curves in Khmer dance."},{"time":41440,"text":"Our backs are arched,"},{"time":43760,"text":"our knees are bent,"},{"time":45680,"text":"our toes are curled,"},{"time":47720,"text":"our elbows are hyperflexed"},{"time":50080,"text":"and our fingers are curved backwards."},{"time":53600,"text":"All of these curves\ncreate a serpentine impression,"},{"time":57280,"text":"and this is important because before\nthe introduction of major religions,"},{"time":62080,"text":"Khmers, and people all over the world\npracticed animism."},{"time":69120,"text":"Serpents were especially important\nin this belief system"},{"time":72040,"text":"because in their fluid,\ncurvilinear movement,"},{"time":76440,"text":"they mimicked the flow of water."},{"time":79520,"text":"So to invoke the serpent\nin your dancing body then"},{"time":83080,"text":"was to conjure the image\nof rivers cutting across the earth:"},{"time":87680,"text":"inspire the flow of life-giving waters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":93440,"text":"As you can see then,"},{"time":94760,"text":"Khmer classical dance\nis a transformation of nature,"},{"time":98200,"text":"of both the physical world around us\nand of our own internal universe."},{"time":103280,"text":"We have four primary\nhand gestures that we use."},{"time":106280,"text":"Can we do them together?"},{"time":108640,"text":"Yeah? OK."}]},{"cues":[{"time":112080,"text":"This is a tree."},{"time":115680,"text":"That tree will grow,"},{"time":118480,"text":"and then it will have leaves."},{"time":122600,"text":"After it has leaves,"},{"time":124160,"text":"it'll have flowers,"},{"time":127960,"text":"and after it has flowers,"},{"time":130280,"text":"it'll have fruit."},{"time":132880,"text":"That fruit will drop"},{"time":135240,"text":"and a new tree will grow."},{"time":137280,"text":"And in those four gestures"},{"time":139360,"text":"is the cycle of life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":148920,"text":"These four gestures are then used"},{"time":151560,"text":"to create a whole entire language\nwith which dancers express themselves."},{"time":156240,"text":"So for example,"},{"time":157560,"text":"I can say,"},{"time":158920,"text":"\"I.\""},{"time":161000,"text":"\"I.\""},{"time":162680,"text":"In dance that would be ..."},{"time":166720,"text":"\"I.\""},{"time":168320,"text":"Or I can say ..."},{"time":171440,"text":"\"Hey you, come here, come here.\""},{"time":174400,"text":"In dance ..."},{"time":179440,"text":"\"Come here,\""},{"time":180720,"text":"or, \"Go, go.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":182640,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":186880,"text":"\"Go.\""},{"time":188320,"text":"And everything from ..."},{"time":192280,"text":"love ..."},{"time":199280,"text":"to sadness,"},{"time":201480,"text":"to --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":202720,"text":"(Stomping)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":203760,"text":"anger"},{"time":205120,"text":"can be expressed\nthrough the dance as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":210160,"text":"There's a certain magic"},{"time":211840,"text":"in the way that things are filtered,\ntransformed and put together"},{"time":216000,"text":"to create limitless possibilities in art."},{"time":219600,"text":"The Khmer word for art,"},{"time":221360,"text":"silapak,"},{"time":222600,"text":"in fact, at its root, means \"magic.\""},{"time":226320,"text":"The artist --"},{"time":227560,"text":"the silapakar,"},{"time":229080,"text":"or the silapakarani, then,"},{"time":230520,"text":"is nothing short of a magician."},{"time":234360,"text":"I am very proud to say"},{"time":236320,"text":"that I belong to a long line of magicians,"},{"time":239360,"text":"from my teacher, Sophiline Cheam Shapiro,"},{"time":242480,"text":"to her teachers who were stars\nin the royal palace,"},{"time":246360,"text":"to the ancient dancers of Angkor"},{"time":249160,"text":"and to the primal villagers"},{"time":250720,"text":"from which the art form\noriginally took life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":255480,"text":"That said,"},{"time":256720,"text":"our cherished heritage was once\nalmost completely destroyed."},{"time":264760,"text":"If you are wearing glasses,"},{"time":266560,"text":"please stand up."},{"time":272760,"text":"If you speak more than one language,"},{"time":275160,"text":"please stand up."},{"time":281320,"text":"If you have light skin,"},{"time":282920,"text":"please stand up."},{"time":291800,"text":"Your glasses meant\nthat you could afford health care."},{"time":296960,"text":"That second or third language you spoke\nindicated your elite education."},{"time":303320,"text":"Your light skin meant\nyou didn't have to work beneath the sun."},{"time":308040,"text":"Under the Khmer Rouge,"},{"time":309600,"text":"who took over Cambodia from 1975 to 1979,"},{"time":313960,"text":"we would all be dead now,"},{"time":316160,"text":"targeted because of our assumed privilege."},{"time":325160,"text":"You see,"},{"time":326400,"text":"the Khmer Rouge looked to Cambodia,"},{"time":328560,"text":"and they saw centuries\nof rigid inequality."},{"time":332200,"text":"The king and the few elites around him"},{"time":334400,"text":"had all the pleasures\nand comforts of the world"},{"time":337280,"text":"while the mass majority\nsuffered from backbreaking labor"},{"time":340520,"text":"and harsh poverty."},{"time":342720,"text":"You don't need a history book\nto see that this is true."}]},{"cues":[{"time":346120,"text":"The Khmer word for \"I,\""},{"time":348360,"text":"for \"me,\""},{"time":350480,"text":"is khnhom."},{"time":353240,"text":"This very same word can also mean \"slave\""},{"time":356960,"text":"and dancers were in fact known\nas knhom preah robam,"},{"time":360720,"text":"or \"slaves of the sacred dance.\""},{"time":365200,"text":"The Khmer Rouge sought\nto end slavery in Cambodia,"},{"time":368280,"text":"yet somehow they turned\neveryone into slaves to do it."},{"time":372400,"text":"They became the oppression\nthat they sought to end."},{"time":376360,"text":"They evacuated the capital"},{"time":378080,"text":"and forced people into labor camps."},{"time":380600,"text":"They tore families apart"},{"time":382520,"text":"and brainwashed children\nagainst their own parents."},{"time":386080,"text":"Everywhere, people were dying\nand being killed,"},{"time":389360,"text":"losing their lives from disease,"},{"time":391440,"text":"overwork,"},{"time":392680,"text":"execution and starvation."},{"time":396640,"text":"The result of this is that an entire third\nof Cambodia's population was lost"},{"time":401360,"text":"in less than four years,"},{"time":403200,"text":"and in that number were 90 percent\nof Khmer dance artists."},{"time":408280,"text":"In other words,"},{"time":409520,"text":"nine out of 10 visions\nfor the tradition and future were lost."}]},{"cues":[{"time":415760,"text":"Thankfully, however,"},{"time":417480,"text":"it was my teacher's teachers,"},{"time":419560,"text":"Chea Samy, Soth Sam On and Chheng Phon,"},{"time":423320,"text":"who would lead the revival of the art form"},{"time":425400,"text":"from the ashes of war and genocide:"},{"time":428760,"text":"one student,"},{"time":430320,"text":"one gesture,"},{"time":431920,"text":"one dance at a time."},{"time":433920,"text":"They wrote the love,"},{"time":435840,"text":"magic,"},{"time":437320,"text":"beauty,"},{"time":438560,"text":"history and philosophy of our lineage"},{"time":440920,"text":"into the bodies of the next generation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":445640,"text":"Nearly 40 years later,"},{"time":447560,"text":"Khmer classical dance\nhas been revived to new heights."},{"time":452080,"text":"Yet somehow it still exists\nin a vulnerable environment."},{"time":456640,"text":"The disastrous effects of war\nstill haunt Khmer people today."},{"time":460840,"text":"It is written in our bodies,"},{"time":462960,"text":"manifested in a genetic passage of PTSD"},{"time":466520,"text":"and in families facing cyclical poverty"},{"time":469320,"text":"and immense cultural rifts\nand language barriers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":474760,"text":"Yet beauty is a most resilient thing."},{"time":479080,"text":"Beauty has this ability\nto grow anywhere and everywhere"},{"time":482960,"text":"at any time."},{"time":485560,"text":"Beauty is what connects people\nthrough time and place."},{"time":490640,"text":"Beauty is a liberation from suffering."},{"time":496400,"text":"As Khmer artists work to revive\nour culture and country,"},{"time":500000,"text":"we find that there are many paths\nin which to move forward into the future."},{"time":506000,"text":"And in a tradition where we often\ndon't know the dancer's names,"},{"time":510360,"text":"who they were,"},{"time":511600,"text":"what their lives were like,"},{"time":513120,"text":"what they felt,"},{"time":515000,"text":"let me propose that we move forward\nhonestly and openly from \"khnhom.\""},{"time":521520,"text":"Khnhom not as in slave,"},{"time":523600,"text":"but as in conscious service."},{"time":526720,"text":"Khnhom:"},{"time":528240,"text":"\"I,\""},{"time":529880,"text":"\"me,\""},{"time":531400,"text":"\"flowering.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":534520,"text":"My name is Prumsodun Ok."},{"time":536800,"text":"I am Khmer,"},{"time":538040,"text":"and I am American."},{"time":540040,"text":"I am the child of refugees,"},{"time":542400,"text":"a creator, a healer,"},{"time":544360,"text":"and a builder of bridges."},{"time":546880,"text":"I am my teacher's first male student"},{"time":549280,"text":"in a tradition understood\nby many as female,"},{"time":552600,"text":"and I founded Cambodia's first\ngay dance company."},{"time":556800,"text":"I am the incarnation\nof the beauty, dreams and power"},{"time":561000,"text":"of those who came before me."},{"time":562960,"text":"The convergence\nof past, present and future,"},{"time":566480,"text":"and of individual and collective."}]},{"cues":[{"time":571080,"text":"Let me then play\nthat ancient and ageless role"},{"time":574320,"text":"of the artist as messenger,"},{"time":576440,"text":"by sharing the words of Chheng Phon"},{"time":580240,"text":"\"A garden with only one type of flower,"},{"time":583840,"text":"or flowers of only one color,"},{"time":585880,"text":"is no good.\""},{"time":588640,"text":"This is a reminder that our strength,"},{"time":592200,"text":"growth,"},{"time":593440,"text":"survival"},{"time":594680,"text":"and very existence,"},{"time":595920,"text":"lies in diversity."},{"time":598680,"text":"It is, however,"},{"time":599960,"text":"a message of courage as well."},{"time":603200,"text":"For a flower does not ask\nfor anyone's permission to bloom."},{"time":608000,"text":"It was born to offer itself to the world."},{"time":611480,"text":"Fearless love is its nature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":614880,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":616120,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}